snippet.textDisplay:
You look good Gab, the blue long sleeve works man. Wear it with confidence and pride. As a big boy myself I know how hard it is to find cloths that look nice and also fit comfortably. When I was a kid and teen one of my worst fear was cloths shopping, it was embarrassing and depressing. The waist fits but the shorts are way to long and baggy or the shirt fits but its down to your knees. Having to buy men's sized cloths as kid and getting made fun of was tough. I know where his mentality about clothing comes from. We see outfits and clothing we like on mannequins and displays but we won't try it on because we know it will never look like that on us. Its depressing so we avoid it and it leads to wearing the same kind of outfit all the time. Like he said he runs straight to sweats area of the store and gets out. As an adult I still avoid cloths shopping. It's not that I don't like cloths, it's I don't want to be depressed when it doesn't fit right. I've left a lot of stores empty handed.


Wear it big man, wear it for all us Fluffys out there.


As usual Fluffy adds a hilarious ending.
